'''bend''', '''bent''', '''bent'''

# To change one's shape into a [[curve]].
#: ''To bow properly, bend at the waist.''

=== Noun ===
'''bend'''

# A [[curve]].
#: ''There's a sharp bend in the road ahead.''
# (''nautical'') A [[knot]] used to tie a [[rope]] onto something.
# (''plural, medicine, diving'') A severe condition caused by excessively quick decompression, causing bubbles of nitrogen to form in the blood.
#: ''A diver who stays deep for too long must ascend very slowly in order to prevent the bends.''

